#### **Day 35: Modern Layouts with Flexbox**

```markdown
# Day 35: Responsive Layouts using Flexbox

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. `display: flex`.
2. Justify Content (Main Axis alignment).
3. Align Items (Cross Axis alignment).
4. `flex-direction` (Row vs Column).

**Learning Summary:**
Before Flexbox, aligning items side-by-side using `float` was a nightmare. Today I learned Flexbox, which makes layout easy. By setting `display: flex` on a container, I can easily center items or spread them out. It is essential for making navigation bars and card grids.

**Code Snippet:**
```css
/* Container */
.navbar {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between; /* Spreads items to edges */
    align-items: center; /* Centers items vertically */
    background-color: navy;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 20px;
}

/* Child Items */
.nav-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 15px; /* Space between links */
}




---HTML---

<nav class="navbar">
    <div class="logo">MyBrand</div>
    <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="#">Home</a>
        <a href="#">Services</a>
        <a href="#">Contact</a>
    </div>
</nav>
